<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910712-0022</DOCNO><DOCID>910712-0022.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Raytheon Co.:   Earnings Rose 4.8%, Sales   Were Flat in Second Period</HL><DATE>07/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   RTN</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Raytheon Co. reported a 4.8% rise in net income for thesecond quarter on flat sales.   Net at the defense electronics concern increased to $151.8million, or $2.30 a share, from $144.8 million, or $2.22 ashare, in the year-ago period. Sales rose to $2.36 billionfrom $2.35 billion.</LP><TEXT>   Raytheon, based in Lexington, Mass., said its electronicsdivision reported improved profitability for the quarter,despite lower sales volume. Raytheon received $244 million innew orders for Patriot missiles for the U.S. and alliednations in the quarter as well as $24 million in initialfunding from a U.S. government order for the sale of aPatriot ground support unit to Israel.   Raytheon's backlog fell 7% to $8.57 billion from $9.23billion, including a $266 million drop in government orders.   For the six months, net rose 3.6% to $285.5 million, or$4.34 a share, from $275.7 million, or $4.22 a share, a yearearlier. Sales rose to $4.61 billion from $4.57 billion.</TEXT></DOC>